Apple-1 Emulator Documentation
================================

Portable Apple-1 emulator in C.  Core code talks only to port.h; each host
gets a port_*.c shim and a term_*.c display backend.

Quick start (POSIX)
-------------------

    ./configure && make
    make check
    ./apple1 -r wozmon.bin

Headless CPU test:

    ./apple1 -H -F wozmon.bin

Documentation map
-----------------

Core (all hosts)
    usage.md            CLI options, .conf files, keyboard (POSIX/MS-DOS)
    configuration.md    Compile-time limits, APPLE1_OMIT_*, port registry
    hardware.md         Memory map, PIA, expansion cards
    debugger.md         Interactive debugger (-g)

Build
    building.md         Autotools, tests, amalgamation, cross-compiles

Platforms (pick your host)
    platforms.md        All ports — POSIX, DOS, Windows, Plan 9, Nspire,
                          VxWorks, FreeRTOS, UnixWare, bare metal
    FREERTOS_DEMO.md    FreeRTOS Posix_GCC simulator
    VXWORKS_RTP.md      VxWorks 7 RTP on QEMU

Deprecated
    manual.md           Legacy GUI-era index — do not use

Project layout
--------------

    main.c              POSIX / Windows / Plan 9 / MS-DOS CLI entry
    main_nspire.c       TI-Nspire entry (no argv parsing)
    cpu.c  bus.c        6502 and system bus
    port.c  term.c      Select port_*.c / term_*.c at compile time
    port_string.c       Freestanding string/format helpers (all builds)
    apple1limit.h       Compile-time limits and defaults
    tools/amalgamate.py Single-file apple1.c generator

What this is
------------

Cycle-oriented Apple-1 with Woz Monitor, optional ACI cassette card, optional
Krusader ROM, CLI debugger, and a 40-column terminal display.

Not included: the old SDL3 GUI (removed).  All interaction is terminal or
host-specific UI (Nspire LCD, DOS conio, etc.).
